            <article class="post-preview">
    <a href="https://darcynorman.net/2024/04/27/2024-week-17/">
        <h2 class="post-title">2024 Week 17</h2>
        
        
        
    </a>

    <p class="post-meta">
        <span class="post-meta">
  
  
  <i class="fas fa-calendar"></i>&nbsp;Posted on April 27, 2024
  
  
  
  
    &nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-clock"></i>&nbsp;8&nbsp;minutes
  
  
    &nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-book"></i>&nbsp;1663&nbsp;words
  
  
  
  
</span>


    </p>
    <div class="post-entry">
        
        ⚙️ Work Still sick. Not wanting to be &ldquo;that guy that keeps coughing and blowing his nose in the office&rdquo;, I took some sick time and worked from home. I&rsquo;m not contagious anymore, and need to be in the office next week. Hopefully my respiratory system cooperates. While preparing for our conference presentation, we collected some links to a couple of videos to support the description of the course. Jana (one of the students in the course) had published one of her video game demos as a video on YouTube - it&rsquo;s a remarkable example of using video games to foster reflection on architecture, experience, and teaching &amp; learning.
        <a class="btn read-more-link btn-secondary" href="https://darcynorman.net/2024/04/27/2024-week-17/" class="post-read-more">Read More</a>
        
